.TH "vmw_cmdbuf_try_alloc" 9 "vmw_cmdbuf_try_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_cmdbuf_try_alloc \- Try to allocate buffer space from the main pool.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" vmw_cmdbuf_try_alloc
.BI "(struct vmw_cmdbuf_man *man "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_cmdbuf_alloc_info *info "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "man" 12
The command buffer manager.
.IP "info" 12
Allocation info. Will hold the size on entry and allocated mm node
on successful return.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Try to allocate buffer space from the main pool. Returns true if succeeded.
If a fatal error was hit, the error code is returned in \fIinfo->ret\fP.
